<p>I'm use <code>formfield_for_foreignkey</code> to filter queryset. All works as expected but when I want to edit object, field is empty and I can' save it.</p>  <pre><code>def formfield_for_foreignkey(self, db_field, request, **kwargs):     if db_field.name == 'item':         kwargs["queryset"] = Item.objects.filter(has_item=False)     return super(TextItemAdmin, self).formfield_for_foreignkey(db_field, request, **kwargs) </code></pre>  <p>It is empty because <code>has_item</code> field from related object become True after object is saved. now I need different queryset depend on object is saved/exist or not.</p>  <p>But <code>if db_field.id:</code> can't be used because it return Attribute error <code>'OneToOneField' object has no attribute 'id'</code> How this can be fixed?</p>